casebody.data:
Joseph WHITE, Plaintiff-Appellant,
v.
DETROIT EAST COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH, Marilyn Snowden, Shirley Calhoun, Doris Sterreh, and Gateway Community Health Provider, Defendants-Appellees. SC: 157683
COA: 340740 Supreme Court of Michigan. May 16, 2018

Order

On order of the Chief Justice, the motion of plaintiff-appellant to waive the statutory filing fees is DENIED. The fee must be paid by June 6, 2018, or the application will be administratively dismissed. MCR 7.317.
